cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the security and privacy of the Tor network, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the impact of DNS traffic on Tor's anonymity, which involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and data privacy (cs.SI). The paper also involves analyzing large datasets (cs.DS) and developing new attack methods (cs.CY).
